    {
      "id": "a98ff9bc70196943504f33addb805424c29d6f42",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 131,
        "name": "Jian Yu",
        "email": "yujian@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "yujian"
      },
      "date": "2011-05-09 03:27:32.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nThanks Chris for the patch.\n\nHowever, I found the \"TF_FAIL\" variable was not defined in acceptance-small.sh. Although it was defined in auster.sh as \"export TF_FAIL=/tmp/tf.fail\", the file was not created anywhere.\n\nAfter doing a comparison with the scripts in master branch, I found the following stuff were missed in b1_8 branch while porting auster from master to b1_8(LU-123):\n\nacceptance-small.sh:\n    export TF_FAIL=$TMP/tf.fail\n\ntest-framework.sh:\ntrap 'print_summary && touch $TF_FAIL && \\\n    echo \"test-framework exiting on error\"' ERR",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
